# **Project Description – CI/CD Pipeline for Airflow Deployment (In Progress)**

## **Context**

This project aims to improve the **deployment process of workflows and components on an Airflow instance**. The current approach relies on sequential API calls, where:

* An artifact is created from a configuration
* The system waits for its availability
* A deployment is then triggered separately

This process is **time-consuming and not optimized**, especially when managing multiple deployments or environments.

***

## **Proposed Solution (In Progress)**

The objective is to design a **complete CI/CD pipeline** that automates and structures both **artifact creation (CI)** and **deployment (CD)** into a unified workflow.

### **1. Continuous Integration (CI) – Artifact Creation**

The CI part focuses on:

* Building a **deployable artifact** for Airflow
* Defining its content through a structured configuration:
  * Source code repositories (Git)
  * Python dependencies
  * System dependencies and storage resources
* Standardizing artifact creation to ensure **consistency and reproducibility**
* Producing an **artifact identifier** that will be reused in the deployment phase [\[groupsg001...epoint.com\]](https://groupsg001-my.sharepoint.com/personal/manar_bensaada_socgen_com1/Documents/Fichiers%20Microsoft%20Copilot%20Chat/deploy_artifact.py)

***

### **2. Continuous Deployment (CD) – Artifact Deployment**

The CD part handles:

* **Deploying the generated artifact** to a target Airflow instance
* Supporting multiple environments (e.g., dev, test, prod) [\[groupsg001...epoint.com\]](https://groupsg001-my.sharepoint.com/personal/manar_bensaada_socgen_com1/Documents/Fichiers%20Microsoft%20Copilot%20Chat/cd.yaml)
* Applying deployment configurations such as:
  * Environment variables
  * Secrets management (vault integration)
  * Synchronization options
* Monitoring the deployment until completion and ensuring it is successful [\[groupsg001...epoint.com\]](https://groupsg001-my.sharepoint.com/personal/manar_bensaada_socgen_com1/Documents/Fichiers%20Microsoft%20Copilot%20Chat/deploy_artifact.py)

***

### **3. End-to-End Workflow**

The pipeline is designed to:

1. Create an artifact from a defined configuration
2. Pass the artifact identifier to the deployment stage
3. Deploy the artifact automatically to the target Airflow instance
4. Track the deployment process and ensure completion

This removes the need for **manual chaining of API calls** and reduces waiting time between steps.

***

## **Importance**

This project contributes to:

* **Automating Airflow deployments** in a structured and reliable way
* Reducing deployment time and operational complexity
* Ensuring **reproducibility and consistency** across environments
* Improving scalability when managing multiple pipelines

Once completed, the solution will provide a **fully integrated CI/CD process**, aligning Airflow deployment with modern DevOps practices and significantly improving efficiency.
